Task on slide 343

With the function you defined in func_drug_conc.R, run the drug concentration model with r2 taking values uniformly between 1/8 and 1/10, and plot the results.

source(file.path("func", "func_drug_conc.R"))

r2_seq <- seq(1/10, 1/8, 0.005)
out_y <- NULL
for (r2_this in r2_seq) {
    out <- deSolve::ode(
            y = c("x" = 1, "y" = 0), func = func_drug_conc,
            times = seq(1, 40, 0.01),
            parms = c("r1" = 1/2, "r2" = r2_this), method = "euler"
    )
    out_y <- cbind(out_y, out[, "y"])
}
out_y
